##Aid Hubei psychologist: under the epidemic situation, can not carry on the moral appraisal simply to the human

Located in the new crown pneumonia fixed-point hospital psychological consultation room.

REPORTER: Yang Shuhongji

There is no prior experience on how to make psychological intervention with the most effective method under the premise of self-safety when the epidemic situation is highly tense. It's up to you to figure out if it's GONNA work.

”

After the outbreak of new crown pneumonia in Hubei Province, the medical staff in the front-line treatment of patients, but also at any time to face the risk of infection.

According to Chen Liangliang, a psychotherapist, this long-term battle with the virus is likely to cause stress Trauma Syndrome among healthcare workers if early intervention is not made. Therefore, as one of the earliest supporting psychotherapists in Wuhan, Chen Liangliang set up the studio in the hospital ward nearest to the medical staff.

He said that in times of high stress, there is no prior experience on how to use psychological intervention in the most effective way while keeping oneself safe. It's up to you to figure out if it's GONNA work.

Here is his dictation

"sometimes I can't help but think it's okay to be infected, at least I don't have to work in shifts. " I could see a huge, unbreakable pressure on her shoulders.

This is in February, I received the epidemic area in Wuhan front-line medical staff consultation encounter a scene.

My name is Chen Liangliang. I am an attending psychiatrist at the Changning District Mental Health Center in Shanghai. In my nine years of practice, I spent most of my time in the General Psychiatric Ward, managing more than 30 beds for patients with major mental disorders, personality disorders and alcohol dependence, and participated in 4 emergency civil defense psychological rescue drills, the clinic also receives regular visitors of all kinds.

As a result of many years of clinical psychotherapy and psychological rescue experience, so in early February 2020, I responded to the call and joined the third group of Shanghai to Hubei Medical Team, as the first group to arrive in Wuhan psychological therapists.

To the average person, a psychiatrist is not much of a concern. But I do know, when this epidemic ravages Wuhan, how to let the witness from the disaster under the impact of stress out of the state, to avoid the future difficult to get rid of the nightmare? How to carry out emergency psychological crisis intervention in an orderly manner is a problem that the city must face and think about.

Recalling that every major disaster and public health emergency that has occurred in our country in recent years, such as the SARS epidemic and the Wenchuan County earthquake, those who experienced it often experienced fear, anxiety and helplessness for a considerable period of time, this is known to the public as the stress-trauma response. In the medical community, early identification, early intervention, can effectively reduce the final development of post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) possibility.

Frankly speaking, at a time of high stress, there is no prior experience on how to conduct psychological intervention in the most effective way while keeping oneself safe. It's up to you to figure out if it's GONNA work.

In order to be able to provide services to patients at the forefront, after several communication, we finally found a place to set up a studio. The office was originally the Maternity Ward Treatment Room, next door to the nurses'lounge, and the top and bottom of the head were the intensive care units for the new pneumonia, the closest we had to the people we worked with.

A nurse walked by several times, nervously setting up the studio, and looked at us through the half-open door with a mixture of anticipation and hesitation in her eyes.

When she was done, she walked in and became the first visitor to the studio.

"I was an ob-gyn here before the outbreak, and I find it particularly difficult to accept the joy that my past work has always brought me in welcoming new life. Now I'm afraid to go into the ward, where I go through despair and death every day. Compared to the past, I feel like I've fallen from heaven to hell... In a conversation of about half an hour, i heard her worry about her colleagues, her guilt about her family, her guilt about her inability to save lives..

I didn't try to interrupt her or give her any advice, because I was already feeling the strain of the past month and she needed to be listened to.

"You described your old job as welcoming life and being happy with it, believing that you had learned to live; but now, perhaps, you need to face death, especially in the intensive-care unit. After all, life and death are compulsory courses for doctors, both the normal state of life. It's not necessarily a different kind of fulfillment."

I tried to give her support and comfort from another dimension.

It is a conventional way of thinking in psychological consultation to break the negative thinking cycle and provide a more comprehensive perspective for "visitors" .

At the end of this sentence, I saw a gleam in the visitor's eye. I'm sure this session worked.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Chen Liangliang hangs on a message board outside the consulting room, covered with messages from medical staff.

From time to time in psychological counseling, I closer to the hearts of these medical staff. With an average age of less than 30, they are bound to feel a bit overwhelmed by the epidemic. That will be infected and do not go to work draw the equivalent of the visitors, is the true portrayal of this true and helpless mood.

Of course, this is just some kind of stress response in people under high pressure. Human Nature is complex, some people will choose to go without hesitation, but some people may instinctively want to step back, to give themselves a buffer time. In the eyes of consultants, moral evaluation can not be simply carried out.

Another medical staff told me that the eight-hour Work Day requires frequent hand disinfection. So that every day after work back to quarantine hotel, still can not get rid of this work mood, will once dazed, often recall, just wash hands? These real cases also reflect the impact of the war on people from the side.

In addition to medical staff, patients with new coronary pneumonia, mental patients are a group of easy to be ignored. In the impact of the epidemic, their fragile psychological defense line more prone to negative, desperate mood. Moreover, drugs for Psychiatric Disorders may interact with drugs for neocoronary pneumonia in terms of their mechanisms of action.

A patient with a history of major depression had the misfortune of contracting new coronary pneumonia. Because of the need for isolation treatment, she was separated from her partner in a different ward, and the lack of a loved one aggravated her depression, which also affected treatment outcomes. Fortunately, through timely communication on Wechat, we are in possession of her daily situation, and timely adjustment of medication. At present, she has been discharged from the hospital, we continue to follow her treatment.

Through Wechat to complete the consultation, minimize contact, while maintaining communication with the bed doctor, to understand the actual effect of the combined medication, and through the connection with experts in the Shanghai Rear, it's all part of our daily routine... to constantly refine our drug regimen.

Spring has come to Wuhan, we give patients psychological counseling, but also more about the spring of the poetic description.

In a recent issue of "psychological tabloids, " my colleagues wrote a little poem for them as they battle the virus.

The poem reads: "When the grass grows and the orioles fly in the February sky, and the willows and willows are drunk with Spring smoke, the virus is merciless, and people are willing to take care of it when they are lying on the sickbed; when three or two flowers come out of the window, the intoxicating spring wind blows in their faces, and the humane early spring is a good season for your recovery. "

And that's what I'm looking forward to right now.
